IP address:34.245.4.99
--------------------------
-sudo: sudo is a program for Unix-like computer operating systems that enables users to run programs with the security privileges of another user, by default the superuser.
we should use it before running most of the commands. It allows us to make changes to system filed and directories
-apt-get: apt-get is a command line tool for interacting with the Advanced Package Tool (APT) library. It allows you to search for, install, manage, update, and remove software. 

I used the following commmands (in order):
checkpoint 1:
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install apache2 mysql-server php-mysql php libapache2-mod-php php-mcrypt php-pear curl php-curl php-cli git
sudo a2enmod rewrite
sudo service apache2 restart

checkpoint 2:
cd /var/www/html/
pwd
sudo git clone https://github.com/NinjaCoder8/stunning-laravel.git

checkpoint 3:
curl -sS https://getcomposer.org/installer | sudo php -- -- installdir=/usr/local/bin -- filename=composer
cd stunning-larvel
sudo composer install

checkpoint 4:
pwd
cp .env.example .env
sudo vim .env (-> i -> Scripting Project -> esc -> :x)
sudo php artisan key:generate

checkpoint 5:
sudo systemctl status apache2
which apache2
/user/sbin/apache2
cd /user/sbin
ls
cd /etc
cd apache2
sudo nano apache2.conf
cd sites-enabled
nano 000-default.conf
sudo service apache2 restart

checkpoint 6:
cd /var/www/html/stunning-larvel/
sudo chgrp -R www-data storage bootstrap/cache (it changes the group of the storage and bootstrap/cache to www-data group)
sudo chmod -R ug+rwx storage bootstrap/cache (sets the file permissions of the "storage" and "bootstrap/cache" directories and their contents to allow the owner and members of the owner's group to read, write, and execute files)

